Find the property tax bill for the property at 225 Garcia Ave, San Leandro, CA 94577 in Alameda County, CA.

Follow these instructions to navigate the county tax portal:
To look up a property tax bill in Alameda County, CA:
1. Navigate to the official Property Tax Portal at https://propertytax.alamedacountyca.gov/.
2. On the landing page, click on the 'Real Property' card (which usually contains icons like a home and work building) to search for secured tax bills.
3. On the search page, ensure the 'Address' tab or search method is selected.
4. Enter the property address (e.g., '225 Garcia Ave, San Leandro') into the search field. 
5. IMPORTANT: You must wait for the auto-suggestion list to appear and click the matching address from the dropdown list. The 'Search' button may remain disabled until a valid suggestion is selected.
6. Click the 'Search' button.
7. On the 'Secured Property Summary' page, locate the 'View Bill - Tracer # [Number]' link and click it.
8. On the 'Secured Property Tax Statement' page, click the 'Print Copy of Bill' button to download or view the PDF version of the tax bill.

Find the property tax bill PDF, download it, upload it to Browser Use, create a presigned URL download link, and provide the download URL in the output under downloadUrl.

IMPORTANT: If the navigation instructions above are inaccurate, incomplete, or if the URLs have changed, provide corrected instructions in the amendedLearnings field and/or the correct URLs in the amendedUrls field. Only provide amendments if something was wrong — leave them empty if the instructions worked correctly.
